<item>
            <title>[FLINK-26484] FileSystem.delete is not implemented consistently</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-26484</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The BlobServer cleanup does not work for the Presto S3 filesystem in case of failure due to some bug in the recursive delete implementation. The &lt;tt&gt;false&lt;/tt&gt; return value is not processed which leads to an error case being &quot;swallowed&quot;, i.e. recursive cleanups do not work in this case (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/prestodb/presto/blob/master/presto-hive/src/main/java/com/facebook/presto/hive/s3/PrestoS3FileSystem.java#L496&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;PrestoS3FileSystem:496&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13431872">FLINK-26484</key>
            <summary>FileSystem.delete is not implemented consistently</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
