                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17501212" author="davidmoravek" created="Fri, 4 Mar 2022 08:12:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This seems to be deep down in the Presto code, with limited options for any overrides. Can you please outline how do you want to tackle this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17501213" author="mapohl" created="Fri, 4 Mar 2022 08:16:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We should implement the recursive deletion in &lt;tt&gt;FileSystem&lt;/tt&gt; and only rely on &lt;tt&gt;FileSystem.deleteFile(path)&lt;/tt&gt; (which is a replacement for &lt;tt&gt;FileSystem.delete(path, false)&lt;/tt&gt;), &lt;tt&gt;FileSystem.exists(path)&lt;/tt&gt;, and &lt;tt&gt;FileSystem.listStatuses(path)&lt;/tt&gt;. We can remove redundant code in &lt;tt&gt;LocalFileSystem&lt;/tt&gt; as well due to that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;LocalFileSystem&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;HadoopFileSystem&lt;/tt&gt; are the only implementations that don&apos;t delegate to another &lt;tt&gt;FileSystem&lt;/tt&gt; implementation internally.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17504128" author="mapohl" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2022 09:29:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Further discussion happened in the PR. No need to backport this change because we don&apos;t do retries in older versions of Flink.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;master: 4907f5fb7033b1f918c4e721a1ccf95878f980a2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
